snippet.textDisplay:
"Fireworks cause extensive air pollution in a short amount of time, leaving metal particles, dangerous toxins, harmful chemicals and smoke in the air for hours and days. Some of the toxins never fully decompose or disintegrate, but rather hang around in the environment, poisoning all they come into contact with. Exposure to fine particles, like those found in smoke and haze, is linked to negative health implications, such as coughing, wheezing, shortness of breath, asthma attacks and even heart attacks, according to the EPA. People at greatest risk for problems are those with heart or lung disease, older adults and children." - terrapass.com/fireworks-impact-environment


Happy polluted new year!

snippet.textDisplay: Unpopular opinion buuuuut....London's display is far too condensed into one small area; focused around what is essentially an overgrown ferris wheel and that density of explosion invariably results in a giant ball of smoke that the fireworks have trouble overcoming. Second to that, the song choices this year left a lot to be desired and finally, why the hell is the London Eye the London spectacle when we have Tower Bridge which in my opinion screams London far more than the Eye. It's a great show as it is but we could do so much better. And I often imagine foreigners watching abroad when we're up to the plate, thinking...'Is that the best thing in London?!'
